  "text": "Firefox's Servo-based CSS style system integrates through a four-component pipeline centered in the layout/style/ directory of the mozilla-firefox/firefox repository.\n\nThe primary entry point is ServoStyleSet (layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h and ServoStyleSet.cpp), a class that acts as the main resolver for CSS styles against the DOM. It manages style sheets, coordinates style resolution across the document, and exposes key methods like StyleDocument() for document-wide styling, ResolveStyleLazily() for on-demand style resolution, and ResolvePseudoElementStyle() for pseudo-element styling.\n\nServoBindings (layout/style/ServoBindings.h) provides the Gecko-to-Servo FFI bridge with extern \"C\" declarations for Servo functions prefixed with \"Servo_\". Key FFI functions include Servo_StyleSet_StyleRuleChanged() for propagating CSS rule modifications from Gecko to Servo, and various Servo_*Rule functions for accessing and manipulating CSS rule objects. These macros expand to declare numerous rule handling functions that form the communication protocol between the C++ side and the Rust Servo engine.\n\nRestyleManager (layout/style/RestyleManager.h and RestyleManager.cpp) schedules and manages style recalculation by monitoring DOM mutations. Methods like ContentInserted() and ContentAppended() respond to element insertions, invalidating styles as necessary. This component integrates with ServoStyleSet through the RestyleHint mechanism to determine which elements and styles require recalculation.\n\nServoUtils (layout/style/ServoUtils.h) provides essential utility functions including IsInServoTraversal() for checking if code is executing during a style traversal, and InitializeServo()/ShutdownServo() for managing the Servo engine lifecycle. A static ServoStyleSet* pointer (sInServoTraversal) tracks the active traversal context across threads.\n\nThe moz.build file (layout/style/moz.build) orchestrates the compilation of the entire style system, listing exports, unified sources (ServoStyleSet.cpp, RestyleManager.cpp), generated headers from cbindgen and Python scripts, and integration with the Servo components at /servo/ports/geckolib. This configuration ensures proper FFI bindings and Rust interoperability through tools like cbindgen that generate ServoStyleConsts.h."
}

